You can try to use a range query something like test:[null TO
"zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz"]
Please note that you might get TooManyBooleanClause Exception, if you =
have
too many of them.

The other thing you can use is with the operator NOT. For all the Empty
fields you can fill them with a string lest say "empty" and then query =
for
-test:empty

Aviran

