On Thursday 28 October 2004 19:03, Justin Swanhart wrote:

> Have you tried making a term query by hand and testing to see if it
> works? =C2=A0
>
> Term t =3D new Term("field", "this is a \"test\"");
> PhraseQuery pq =3D new PhraseQuery(t);

That's not a proper PharseQuery, it searches for *one*=20
term >this is a "test"< which is probably not what one wants. You=20
have to add the terms one by one to a PhraseQuery.

